node.text: My fridge so desperately needed this 😅 I just cleaned out and reorganized the pantry a couple weeks ago so it was only fair that the fridge be next. Don’t ask me about the freezer though, I think I’m still too afraid to look in there. So, how long will the fridge stay organized like this? Ehhh, probably until our next grocery trip when I just throw everything in here but I’m hoping for the best. You never know 😂 Maybe the “white” rice I found in here is enough to motivate me to keep it clean....because that was embarrassing 🙈 Anyone else with a “lost in the back of the fridge” horror story? Mine usually end in me throwing away the ENTIRE Tupperware container because it’s just not worth it to open it 🥴🙅🏼‍♀️

node.text:
I should add a disclaimer to start: our family really likes the F bomb but it’s spongebob censored! 🤣 
In order: 
➡️Blake 
➡️His dad & brother: We always play skipbo together so we taped a “Emily is pregnant” note to the first card they would play for the game 
➡️My dad & mom: it was my dads birthday that month so we put an “engaged, married, expecting” card with his gift 
➡️Blake’s mom & grandpa: We told his mom we were hosting a cookout before we move & wanted her to pick her favorite invitations (she loves to party plan!) but both “invitations” were the announcement cards 
➡️My grandma & grandpa: we dropped by to give my grandma the announcement card because we always get little gifts for each other. 
❤️ Our family is ecstatic. We can’t wait for March!

node.text: Hello again 👋🏼 I’m officially commencing fall on this account because I physically don’t want to do anything else 🤣 I think I have a pumpkin for a brain. Lmao. I’ve been waiting to make this pumpkin fireplace for months now and I couldn’t wait another second to sit here and enjoy a good fall movie with an @oak.hill.farms pumpkin soufflé candle burning! Just pretend it isn’t 104° today, ok? 😬 When are y’all pulling out the fall decor?

node.text:
I was a new human today 🤩 I remember pre-baby me thinking “how the heck do moms not have at least 20 minutes to get ready?” Lollllll. These days it’s either a meal or makeup: pick it. But I got the 20 minutes today and I finally felt like me 🙌🏼 So on that note, here’s 9 things about me. But there’s 10, because one of them is a lie. Do you know which one it is? 🤫

1. I got my first tattoo when I was 18 and told my mom it was henna. She believed me….for a little while.

2. I stood in one spot in NYC for 16 hours without using the bathroom or eating just to watch the ball drop on NYE.

3. I was too afraid to quit my job at Panera so I told them I had to get Advil out of my car and left.

4. I still doggy paddle when I swim.

5. I once ate a chocolate donut covered in ants on accident.

6. My first job was at Chuck E. Cheese.

7. I’m obsessed with those live oyster shell pearl opening videos on Facebook. It’s like ASMR.

8. We didn’t look at any other houses before we bought this one.

9. I can’t burp. 

10. I got stuck upside down on a rollercoaster at universal for 20 minutes.

**Answered in stories: it’s 10 😉**

node.text: What a fun few years it’s been. Life changing actually, because our home brought me here and I’ll always be so thankful for that ❤️ When we come back from our trip, we’re going to start prepping to list our home and pack up the storage room. I’ll just be over here crying if you need me. I love this house so much. 🥲

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Emily | DIY & Ducks on June 06, 2021 tagging @infarmhousefashion. May be an image of 4 people, child, people standing and indoor.

node.text: How many adults does it take to cut wood at angle? Idk, because we certainly could’ve used an extra brain today LOL 😂 But we still managed with 4 of us...although I won’t point any fingers at who slowed the DIY crew down (hint: he’s the tallest, yet smallest 🤫) So there’s another round of board & batten for the gram. I think I’ve attempted just about every type of design now, no? 😂  This one was definitely the trickiest yet but it’s going to look awesome when it’s finished! This room is at @infarmhousefashion home in her game room. So many fun ideas happening in here—I’ll keep ya updated! 🤩 Anyone working on any fun projects? 👇🏼
